<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEEKEND BOX OFFICE; STALLONE AND STONE DRAW IN THE FANS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVID J. FOX 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Despite downbeat reviews and trailers that elicited laughter in theaters, the 
action film "The Specialist" rode on the draw of its two stars--Sylvester 
Stallone and Sharon Stone--to an opening weekend of $14.3 million--the biggest 
October opening ever. The total beats the $14.2-million record established only 
last year by "Demolition Man," in which Stallone starred with Wesley Snipes. 
</P>
<P>
 "The Specialist" notwithstanding, the weekend total of $53.6 million was still 
down 14% from the comparable period a year ago. 
</P>
<P>
 The only other major opening was the romantic comedy "Only You," starring 
Marisa Tomei and Robert Downey Jr., which grossed an unimpressive $5.7 million. 
