<HEADLINE>
<P>
NATION IN BRIEF; UTAH; MORMON FEMINIST MAY BE DISCIPLINED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Mormon feminist who wrote that God has a woman as an equal partner in heaven 
faces ecclesiastical discipline. Janice Allred, who could be excommunicated at 
a disciplinary hearing Wednesday before her local church board, believes an 
essay she wrote in an independent journal is to blame.In the essay, published 
in the journal Dialogue, she said that there is a "heavenly mother" who is 
God's equal partner in heaven. Church leaders have said that while the 
existence of a heavenly mother is a logical and reasonable doctrine, the church 
has not said whether she is God's equal. One of the standards defined by the 
9-million-member church's all-male hierarchy is strict obedience to a 
prohibition on public contradiction or criticism of the leadership. Of the 
disciplinary hearing, Allred said: "I don't see it simply as an issue of being 
able to publish one article. It's an issue of freedom to speak and write." 
</P>
</TEXT>
