<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: CENTURY CITY; EXPANSION 
OF RECYCLING PROGRAM ENTERS LAST PHASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Los Angeles municipal officials marked the rollout Monday of the final phase 
of the city's curbside recycling program, with a Western-themed fair in the 
Century Plaza Towers' courtyard. The event completes the expansion of the 
city's 4-year-old recycling program. 
</P>
<P>
 The program, begun in El Sereno in September, 1990, is the largest such effort 
undertaken by a U.S. city. 
</P>
</TEXT>
