<HEADLINE>
<P>
STUNTMAN HURT AT THEME PARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A stuntman in the "Miami Vice" show at Universal Studios fell off a jet ski 
during rehearsal Monday and suffered minor injuries. 
</P>
<P>
 The performer, Joe Box, 25, was treated and released from St. Joseph Medical 
Center in Burbank, a hospital spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
 The show, based on the once-popular television series about vice detectives in 
Miami, opened in 1987 and features a speedboat ride through a simulated lagoon, 
among other fast-paced stunts. 
</P>
<P>
 Accounts of what led to the accident differed. Universal spokesman Michael 
Gray said the stuntman fell off his ski. But paramedics said they responded to 
a report that Box was hit by another jet skier. 
</P>
