<HEADLINE>
<P>
SEEDED PLAYERS WIN AT WHEELCHAIR EVENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The eight seeded players won in first-round play of the men's U.S. Open 
Wheelchair tennis championships Monday at The Racquet Club of Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
 Matt McManus of Coral Gables, Fla., beat Katsunari Yamamoto of San Diego, 6-1, 
6-0, and second-seeded Rocky LeBlanc of Goodlettsville, Tenn., beat Shuhoi 
Ishimoto of Japan, 6-1, 6-2. 
</P>
<P>
 Admission is free to the tournament, which continues today through Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
