<HEADLINE>
<P>
INSIDE VALLEY BUSINESS; AFTER THE QUAKE, MALLS PIN HOPES ON THE HOLIDAYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Many Valley shopping malls that escaped major earthquake damage are enjoying a 
10% to 30% jump in sales over the same time last year.Now they hope for the 
best Christmas season in years, which is especially important because 40% of 
retailers' sales come during the holiday season. 
</P>
<P>
 While some Valley malls are benefiting from pent-up consumer demand, layoffs 
in many industries continue to plague the region, warned John Golisch, chief 
retail consultant in Southern California for Arthur Andersen & Co. He wonders 
if the sales gains at some stores will last because they have come at the 
expense of closed malls and from an influx of earthquake assistance funds. 
</P>
<P>
 See Valley Business, page 4. 
</P>
</TEXT>
