</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Simi Valley residents concerned about transit services for the disabled are 
being asked to apply for the city's transit advisory committee. 
</P>
<P>
 In order to qualify, applicants must either be disabled or use the city's 
Dial-A-Ride bus service. 
</P>
<P>
 The city is filling three vacancies on the five-member committee, which meets 
four times a year to review a range of transit service issues including 
policies, availability, accessibility, safety and training. 
</P>
<P>
 The application deadline is Friday. For more information, call Simi Valley 
Transit at 527-2441. SARA CATANIA 
