<HEADLINE>
<P>
VANDALS WENT TOO FAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Five students are suspended in the vandalism of a rival school (Sept. 30), and 
the damage reported included graffiti on the exterior of the gym, yellow paint 
on lockers, raw eggs tossed against a building, whipping cream smeared on the 
handball courts and dog food dumped near Buena High's school sign. 
</P>
<P>
 Yet the assistant principal of Ventura High is quoted as saying, "I agree that 
their intentions were honorable and spirited," but went on to say that the 
outcome was different.More appalling was the Ventura High principal: "To an 
extent it's normal kid behavior that just goes a little too far. I don't see 
that it's a big deal." 
</P>
<P>
 Please tell me that the principal and assistant principal have been misquoted. 
Otherwise, I am repelled by the twisted values which their statements imply. 
Any disrespect by students to persons or property should be unacceptable to 
school officials, if the inculcation of values has any place in the school 
curriculum. "Just a little too far" indeed. 
</P>
<P>
 M.H. SHAGAM 
</P>
<P>
 Ojai 
</P>
