<HEADLINE>
<P>
CLUBS TO GIVE $35,000 TO CHILD CARE CENTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By IRA E. STOLL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Abused, abandoned and neglected children will benefit from more than $35,000 
raised by the Camarillo Rotary Clubs in a golf tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 Leaders of the city's two Rotary clubs will present a check at noon on 
Wednesday to Casa Pacifica, a residential children's crisis care center in 
Camarillo, officials at the center said. 
</P>
<P>
 Casa Pacifica officials said the money was raised by 110 golfers in July at 
the second annual "Care for Kids Golf Classic," which included a dinner and an 
auction. 
</P>
<P>
 The Rotary clubs have pledged $250,000 to help build a library and learning 
center at the newly opened center. IRA E. STOLL 
</P>
</TEXT>
