<HEADLINE>
<P>
DONATIONS OVERLOOKED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A major contribution, $1,000 from the Oxnard Elks Lodge, was overlooked in the 
Sept. 24 article regarding the new video security system at the Oxnard Public 
Library. Additionally, there have been many contributions from members of 
Friends of the Library and other concerned citizens. 
</P>
<P>
 The Ventura County Amateur Radio Club kicked off the fund-raising for the 
system with a $1,000 donation in April, 1993. The club recently gave another 
$1,000 for the second phase of the system. 
</P>
<P>
 We appreciate the support that has been shown for this and other Friends 
projects. Friends of the Library strives to help the Oxnard Public Library in 
its continuing service to our community. 
</P>
<P>
 FELICITY A. HARPER 
</P>
<P>
 Oxnard 
</P>
<P>
 Felicity Harper is president of the Oxnard Friends of the Library.  
</P>
</TEXT>
