<P>
 Police have arrested a man identified as one of two suspects in the armed 
robbery of a Thrifty store last week. 
</P>
<P>
 Johnnie Lumica Stocker, 20, of Riverside was arrested Friday at the Probation 
Department in Orange after detectives lured him there to inquire about a 
probation violation. 
</P>
<P>
 Sgt. Mike Handfield, who headed the team investigating the case, said that 
Stocker and a companion are suspected of robbing the Thrifty in the 9000 block 
of Chapman Avenue on Oct. 3. 
</P>
<P>
 According to their investigation, Handfield said, two men tied up the 
employees at gunpoint and fled with about $2,600 in cash. 
</P>
<P>
 Handfield said that the suspects wore ski masks. Stocker became a suspect 
after a store employee told police he may have recognized the voice of one of 
the robbers as that of Stocker's, who used to work at the store, Handfield 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Handfield said that investigators contacted Stocker, informed him about "a 
minor probation violation" and arrested him when he inquired about it at the 
Probation Department. 
</P>
<P>
 Stocker was on probation for an offense as a juvenile, Handfield said. He is 
being held at County Jail while awaiting his arraignment. 
</P>
<P>
 Following Stocker's arrest, search warrants were served in Huntington Beach 
and Riverside, but the second suspect is still being sought, Police Lt. John 
Woods said.BERT ELJERA 
