<TEXT>
<P>
 Undercover police arrested 37 men for soliciting prostitution during a sting 
operation Friday night and early Saturday) morning. 
</P>
<P>
 Three female officers posing as prostitutes were involved in the 6 1/2-hour 
operation, which targeted an increase in prostitution along Harbor Boulevard, 
Lt. John Woods said After an absence of two to three years, prostitutes appear 
to have returned to the street, Woods said, apparently chased out of Anaheim 
and Santa Ana.Both those cities have created police programs that target men 
soliciting prostitution. 
</P>
<P>
 "We have received information that activities have begun to reoccur," Woods 
said. He added that the "john operation," conducted from 8:30 p.m. Friday to 3 
a.m. Saturday, will be repeated. 
