COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: WESTMINSTER; LIBRARY COLLECTION SALE TO BRING IN $41,000 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON NALICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Westminster School District has approved a plan to sell the library 
collection at Virginia K. Boos Elementary School for $41,000 and spend the 
money on new books for the district's other campuses. 
</P>
<P>
 The Board of Trustees voted unanimously last week to sell the collection, 
which includes about 7,000 books. The school closed in June. Live Oak School 
District in Santa Cruz County purchased the collection, district spokeswoman 
Audrey Brown said. 
</P>
<P>
 School officials initially hoped to get about $27,000 for the book collection, 
Brown said, "so this is quite a bit more money than we expected. We'll be able 
to buy almost 3,000 new books." JON NALICK 
</P>
</TEXT>
