<HEADLINE>
<P>
SUPERIOR INDUSTRIES POSTS 36% PROFIT INCREASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Superior Industries International Inc., a Van Nuys supplier of aluminum car 
wheels, benefiting from strong demand for autos, reported earnings and sales 
gains for its third quarter and nine months ended Sept. 30. 
</P>
<P>
 In the September quarter, Superior had a profit of $12.6 million, a 36% 
increase from its $9.29 million in net income a year earlier.Its sales rose 
30%, to $107.4 million from $82.8 million. 
</P>
<P>
 For the recent nine-month period, the company earned $40.6 million, up 24% 
from a $32.6-million profit a year before, while sales grew 16% to $334 million 
from $287.8 million. 
</P>
<P>
 Superior attributed the improved results to production remaining high at a 
time when auto assembly plants typically retool for new model changeovers. 
</P>
<P>
 But it noted that operating profits were squeezed somewhat by the start of 
production at its plant in Chihuahua, Mexico, and expansion of its 
Fayetteville, Ark., plant. 
</P>
</TEXT>
