<HEADLINE>
<P>
ELECTRO RENT CORP. REPORTS 1ST-QUARTER PROFIT UP 34% 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Electro Rent Corp., a Van Nuys-based company that rents computer equipment, 
said its profit for the fiscal first quarter that ended Aug. 31 was $3.55 
million, up 34% from $2.65 million in the same period a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
 Revenues were up slightly to $27.8 million from $27.5 million in the first 
quarter last year. 
</P>
<P>
 The company said sales in its rental and leasing operations improved slightly 
while bank borrowings decreased during the quarter. 
</P>
