<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Chris Woodyard, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 America West Airlines began offering vacation packages to Orange County last 
week, a move that could boost the local tourism industry. 
</P>
<P>
 America West Vacations, the airline's tour packaging division, is marketing 
the three-day air fare and hotel deals for $124 per person from Phoenix, $194 
from Portland, Ore., or Seattle, and $334 from Columbus, Ohio. 
</P>
<P>
 "Southern California is one of the country's most popular year-round vacation 
destinations," said Karen Cahn, manager of California and Florida marketing for 
America West Vacations.  
</P>
<P>
 The packages include tickets to Knott's Berry Farm in Buena Park, which has a 
marketing agreement with America West. 
</P>
<P>
 The packages aid a tourism industry that is bouncing back from recession. 
Though hotels and attractions are still heavily discounting, recent hotel 
occupancy figures attest to the Southland's appeal as a vacation destination.  
</P>
<P>
 After riots, earthquakes, fires and floods, the worst may be over. 
