ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY: MOVING QUICKLY, RENO AIR TO BEGIN FLIGHTS FROM JOHN 
WAYNE NOV. 1 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Reno Air Inc., moving quickly after Orange County supervisors changed airport 
access rules, said Monday that it will begin five daily nonstop flights out of 
John Wayne Airport on Nov. 1 and add a sixth on Nov. 3. 
</P>
<P>
 The discount airline's first five daily flights will go to San Jose, with 
connecting flights available to Portland, Seattle and Colorado Springs.The 
remaining nonstop flight will go to Reno. 
</P>
<P>
 One-way coach fares to San Jose will be as low as $34.50 for companion tickets 
and $49 for advance purchase, while coach fares to Reno will be as low as $44 
one way. 
</P>
<P>
 Reno Air leapfrogged over other airlines waiting for access to the airport 
through its affiliation with American Airlines. The county's Board of 
Supervisors voted Oct. 4 to allow such arrangements to take precedence over the 
airport's waiting list of carriers wishing to begin service at John Wayne. 
</P>
