<P>
 A 38-year-old worker on an earthquake-repair project fell two stories from a 
scaffold Monday, impaling his upper arm on a wrought-iron fence. 
</P>
<P>
 He was taken with part of the fence still transfixing his arm to Northridge 
Hospital Medical Center, where he was listed in serious but stable condition 
after undergoing surgery to remove it, a hospital spokeswoman said. 
</P>
