<P>
THE WEEK AHEAD: OSLO; NOBEL LOOKS MIDEAST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Middle East leaders who negotiated peace between Israel and the 
Palestinians are mentioned most often as favorites for the 1994 Nobel Peace 
Prize, which will be announced in the Norwegian capital Friday . 
</P>
<P>
 Israeli Prime Minister Yitzhak Rabin, Foreign Minister Shimon Peres and 
Palestine Liberation Organization Chairman Yasser Arafat were among the 117 
men, women and organizations nominated. 
</P>
<P>
