<P>
WHAT'S THE DEAL: BODY WATCH; MINI AND MAXI WAYS TO CHANGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ELAINE KO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 If you're bored with your hair color and think it's time for a change (whether 
minor or drastic), here are some suggestions for tinting, highlighting, 
lightening or dyeing:  
</P>
<P>
 * Lemons (for blond highlights), anywhere from free to 49 cents each. 
</P>
<P>
 * Peroxide, 4 ounces, $2.43. 
</P>
<P>
 * Cranberry juice (for burgundy tints), half-gallon, $2.49. 
</P>
<P>
 * A Touch of Sun by Clairol, 4.7-ounce spray, $3.23. 
</P>
<P>
 * L'Oreal Performing Preference shampoo-in permanent hair color, one 
application, $7.49. 
</P>
<P>
 * Beauty salon full-treatment dyeing, about $30 per visit. 
</P>
<P>
 * Wig, human hair, shoulder length, $54.95 and up. ELAINE KO 
</P>
